; FOUND by P6d numeric-depth sweep (ESH-0123). The parser REJECTS a rational
; literal whose numerator or denominator exceeds int64 ("invalid rational
; literal"), even though the same value is constructible at runtime via (/ p q)
; and small literals like 22/7 parse fine. This is a lexer/parser gap distinct
; from the runtime exactness contagion (ESH-0105/0110).
;   100000000000000000000/3   -> compile error: invalid rational literal
(require stdlib)
(display 100000000000000000000/3) (newline)
(display "OK rational-literal-bignum") (newline)
